main event: A cube-shaped object, three feet square, was observed at an estimated 3,000 feet altitude in Ellwood, Pennsylvania in September 1956. The object moved up and northeast before disappearing at an estimated 10,000 feet, and it was seen visually through binoculars for 61 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as cube-shaped and three feet square, which is an unusual and distinct shape for a UFO.
The duration of the sighting was relatively long, lasting for 61 minutes, allowing for detailed observation.
The estimated altitude of the object changed significantly during the sighting, starting at 3,000 feet and disappearing at 10,000 feet, suggesting dynamic movement.
The conclusion drawn was that the sighting was likely caused by a balloon, based on factors such as duration, winds, and the description of the sighting.
The observation was made by a janitor at Ellwood, Pennsylvania, adding a specific and credible witness to the report.
